From the K distribution, the LOLP of a solar power plant operating at daily basis (e.g., the Tesla’s power plant at Kauai, Hawaii) can be estimated as the fraction of days with solar radiation lower than the demand value,1LOLP=∫0KDf(K)dK,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
