				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$K_D = [1 + \gamma _T(T - T_r)]K_{D,r},$$\end{document}where the temperature factor, γT, is about 0.0045/K, Tr is the reference temperature, and KD,r is the specific value of K that is just enough to generate the demanding energy at the reference temperature. With this change, the corresponding LOLP becomes,13LOLP=∫0[1+γT(T−Tr)]KD,rf(K)dK.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
